akrotiri (greek: ακρωτήρι, literally cape, turkish: ağrotur) is a village within the aktrotiri sovereign base area, which forms part of the british overseas territory of akrotiri and dhekelia. it is the only village in the western sba with a significant non-military population. the village contains two small churches dedicated to st. cross and st. george. to the south is a site called kurias (or kouria, greek: κουριά) containing the ruins of an ancient settlement. of the place stefano lusignan in his description de toute l'isle de cypre (paris, 1580) says: "cury est une ville antique, située au milieu du promontoire des chats."